{0 'The Commodity Credit Corporation, CCC,has accepted bids for export bouses to cover sales of 150,000tonnes of U.S. barley to Saudi Arabia, the U.S. AgricultureDepartment said. The CCC accepted three bonus offers from one exporter whichaveraged 40.88 dlrs per tonne, it said. The barley is for delivery August 15-November 30 in threeshiments of 50,000 tonnes each. The bonus awards were made to Louis Dreyfus Corporation andwill be paid in the form of commodities from CCC stocks. An additional 350,000 tonnes of U.S. barley are stillavailable to Saudi Arabia under the Export Enhancement Programinitiative annnounced on May 15, 1987, it said. Reuter',1 GRAIN}
