{0 'The Agricultural Stabilization andConservation Service announced several temporary steps toenable it to respond more quickly to the high demand forCommodity Credit Corp.-owned soybeans. The CCC has suspended its practice of contacting storingwarehousemen before selling soybeans for cash to a third party,said Collyn Peterson, deputy director in the ASCS Kansas Cityoffice. In addition, he said, minimum quantities for sales will be25,000 bushels, or all of a warehouse total inventory if lessthan that. ASCS has added telephone lines to handle calls from thoseinterested in buying soybeans, Peterson said. Reuter',1 OILSEED}
