{0 'The Japanese economy has bottomed outafter an extended period of stagnation, Finance Minister KiichiMiyazawa told a press conference. But he said he was not too optimistic about the state ofthe economy as the employment situation was still shaky incertain regions of the country. Yesterday, the Finance Ministry said its quarterlycorporate survey showed that the economy was showing increasingsigns of recovery. REUTER',1 GNP}
{0 'The Central Bank has issued 8.29 billionTaiwan dlrs worth of certificates of deposit (CDs), raisingtotal CD issues so far this year to 228.27 billion, a bankofficial told Reuters. The CDs, with maturities of six months, one and two years,bear interest rates ranging from 4.05 to 5.25 pct, she said. The issues are intended to help curb the growth of the M-1bmoney supply which is expanding due to the rise in Taiwan\'sforeign exchange reserves, now at some 60 billion U.S. Dlrs. REUTER',1 MONEY-SUPPLY}
