{0 'Carter Hawley Hale Stores Inc saidit has set June 29 as the record date for shareholders votingon the company\'s proposed restructuring at its annual meeting. The company has yet to set a date for the meeting, but hassaid it will be held before the end of August. Under the proposal, Carter Hawley would split into aspecialty store company and a department store company. Shareholders would get 17-dlrs in cash and a share in eachof the two new companies for each existing common share theyhold. The restructuring was announced in December, after CarterHawley rejected a buy-out offer by Retail Partners. Reuter',1 ACQ}
